snippet.title: Watch Colin Jost roast Biden, Trump and others at White House Correspondents’ Dinner
snippet.description: Saturday Night Live star Colin Jost roasts politicians including President Joe Biden and former President Donald Trump at the 2024 White House Correspondents’ Dinner. #CNN #News

Ah, watching Colin Jost at the White House Correspondents’ Dinner was like witnessing a masterful tightrope walker tiptoeing through a minefield of political absurdity. His sharp wit and biting commentary served as a beacon in the murky swamp of modern politics, illuminating the nonsensical twists and turns that define our current reality.

As he skewered President Biden with razor-sharp quips, Jost couldn’t help but marvel at the baffling paradoxes of our time. How is it, he mused, that Biden’s opponent—a man draped in more indictments than a crime boss at a mob summit—could even be considered a contender for the highest office in the land? It’s as if the inmates in a maximum-security prison looked at him and said, “Hey, tone it down a bit, buddy. You’re making us look bad.”

But the real punchline lay in the eerie echoes of history. Hitler, the master manipulator who turned a democratic nation into a totalitarian regime with the precision of a mad scientist conducting a diabolical experiment. And while Hitler may be long gone, his playbook remains, its pages yellowed with age but its lessons as chillingly relevant as ever.

In a world where Orange Hitler lurks in the shadows, hungry for power and primed to exploit the fears and prejudices of the masses, Jost’s words served as both a warning and a call to action. For if we’re not careful, he suggested, we could find ourselves hurtling down a path paved with demagoguery and despair, with only our laughter to light the way.
